# ECC rules vendoring is RETIRED (2026-07-02): the full upstream rules tree
# ships inside the ECC marketplace clone
# (~/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/ecc/rules/) wherever the plugin is installed,
# so local copies bought sync code and churn for nothing.
#
# Claude Code natively auto-loads every .md under ~/.claude/rules at launch
# (verified live in a cloud session, 2026-07-02): a `paths:` frontmatter scopes
# a rule to sessions where matching files are in context; no frontmatter means
# it loads EVERY session. Retirement-era docs said "nothing auto-loads
# ~/.claude/rules" -- that observation came from fresh cloud clones, where the
# untracked vendored dirs simply did not exist. Leftover vendored language dirs
# (common/ cpp/ python/ rust/ typescript/ web/) on older machines are therefore
# NOT inert: the language dirs activate on matching files, and common/ + web/
# (no `paths:`) load every session. Delete them; this ignore keeps them from
# ever being committed in the meantime.
#
# Only our OWN rules are version-controlled, under claude/rules/personal/
# ("personal" = authored by us, not vendored; the dir serves both the personal
# and work config dirs via the claude/rules symlink). Tracked by the whitelist
# below.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/personal/
